          "The <strong>first step in accepting responsibility for a mistake</strong> is to <strong>admit/acknowledge it</strong>, then fix it — not to make excuses or blame others (EI:075). DECA reliably tests this 'admit it first' sequence.",
          "Taking responsibility builds trust and a stronger professional reputation — the exam rewards ownership over defensiveness."
